default&#xa0;
defaultQ123 default&#xa0; 
defaultChair:default How significant would you say the LSE is compared with other listing platforms?
defaultDavid Lawtondefault: It is by far the dominant 
defaultUK
default listed platform.
default 
defaultThere are four exchanges that, under the FCA’s rules, are able to operate a listed market, and the LSE accounts for the vast majority of listed securities that are traded.
default&#xa0;
defaultQ124 default&#xa0; 
defaultChair:default What makes it so dominant, do you think?
defaultDavid Lawtondefault: It is partly a question of history
default: h
defaultistorically, it was the only 
defaultUK
default market for trading securities and therefore has benefited from that legacy of history.
default 
defaultSecondly, the nature of markets is that liquidity begets liquidity
default—
defaultthey are network
default&#x2011;
defaulttype
default arrangements
default—and i
defaultssuers and investors are attracted to marketplaces where there is market depth.
default&#xa0;
defaultQ125 default&#xa0; 
defaultChair:default What does a company have to do to be listed here in 
defaultLondon
default, on the FTSE and the AIM?
defaultDavid Lawtondefault: Th
defaultis
default might be a moment just to describe a little bit more carefully what “listed” means.
default 
defaultStrictly speaking, the Official List is a list of securities that meet certain criteria set by us.
default 
defaultSeparately, exchanges offer marketplaces for the trading of securities.
default 
defaultAs we have talked about already, the LSE offers the largest market for the trading of listed securities.
default 
defaultAIM is a junior market operated by the LSE and, in fact, is for unlisted securities, so securities that are traded on AIM are not on the Official List. 
default In order to be listed, an issuer would have to take a number of steps.
default 
defaultThe first is, typically, it would have to appoint some advisers to work with it to prepare it to go through the process.
default 
defaultIf an issuer wanted to be on the premium segment of the Official List—I can talk a bit more about what that means in due course—it would also have to appoint a sponsor, typically an investment bank, to co
default&#x2011;
defaultordinate the process. It would have to produce a prospectus, which sets out details about the company, its business plan, its revenue expectations and so on, in order to provide investors with all the information that they need to make an informed assessment about the pricing of the security, and then it would need to apply to us for admission to the List and satisfy the admission criteria.
default 
defaultIn parallel, it would also need to apply to an exchange to be admitted to trading.
default&#xa0;
defaultQ126 default&#xa0; 
defaultChair:default Just going back to your comments about AIM, if it is not listed—forgive my layman’s ignorance on this—how can its shares be traded?
default How would
default would-be investors know how to trade with them or know that they are there to be traded?
defaultDavid Lawtondefault: Exchanges offer different types of market.
default 
defaultThere are the listed markets that we have talked about, which obviously have strong symbiosis with the Official List that we run but, under European legislation exchanges are also able to operate junior markets in unlisted but still transferrable securities.
default 
defaultIt is the nature of the securities that makes them 
defaulttradeable
default, but they are not on our Official List.
defaultChair:default I still do not understand from what you have said how somebody knows that they can trade that company’s stock.
defaultDavid Lawtondefault: AIM has its own rules that govern the admission of securities to that market, and there are rules for issuers as well as for the trading.
default 
defaultThe structure of those rules actually more broadly mirrors the structure of the listing regime, but the details are set by the London Stock Exchange.
