defaultQ144 default&#xa0; 
defaultAnn defaultMcKechindefault:default Thank you, Mr Lawton.
default 
defaultThat is very helpful.
default 
defaultCan I just go on to more general questions?
default 
defaultYou mentioned in your written evidence that mineral companies have slightly modified admission criteria
default—i
defaultn fact, considerably less than for companies that are not in this sector.
default 
defaultCould you run through why there are different premium criteria for these companies?
defaultDavid Lawtondefault: Yes indeed.
default 
defaultIt is largely due to the technical nature of the industry.
default 
defaultIt is certainly not the case that the different criteria imply a lesser standard.
default 
defaultFor the premium listed company, a normal company would need to have what is called a three
default&#x2011;
defaultyear track record, in other words be able to demonstrate three years of ongoing business
default,
default properly audited.
default 
defaultIn relation to mineral companies, the thing that investors particularly focus on is an independent expert’s report on the reserves and mineral assets that they have access to, so that takes the place of the three
default&#x2011;
defaultyear track record.
default 
defaultThe other criterion that applies to a normal company is that you have to have control of the business.
default 
defaultIn relation to the mineral sector, a typical business practice might be to have co
default&#x2011;
defaultinvestments
default or production
default&#x2011;
defaultsharing
default arrangements.
default 
defaultTherefore, for that type of company, we do not insist that you have control of your business, but we simply insist that you have a range of such investments.
default 
defaultThose two differences really just reflect the technical nature of the minerals sector.
default&#xa0;
defaultQ145 default&#xa0; 
defaultAnn defaultMcKechindefault:default Is the report from the sponsor any different for a mineral company from what it would be for a non
default&#x2011;
defaultmineral
default company?
defaultDavid Lawtondefault: No.
default&#xa0;
defaultQ146 default&#xa0; 
defaultAnn defaultMcKechindefault:default If you are entering into co
default&#x2011;
defaultpartnership with other partners as alliances, surely that might necessitate further investigation and a more thorough investigation to ensure that the company’s activities are such that they are not going to bring the listing into disrepute.
defaultDavid Lawtondefault: There are two important steps in relation to this admission process.
default 
defaultThe first is that the prospectus that we talked about earlier clearly has to disclose all the relevant information about the company and its investment prospects, including the details of any production
default&#x2011;
defaultsharing
default arrangements and so on.
default 
defaultRegarding the sponsor’s due diligence, when I said that the sponsor’s report is the same, the attestations that they make and the questions they answer are the same but, of course, in relation to a particular company’s circumstances, the amount of due diligence and the areas that need to be probed in order to be able to reach those attestations may be different.
default&#xa0;
defaultQ147 default&#xa0; 
defaultAnn defaultMcKechindefault:default The sponsor is presumably paid a fee to carry out the due diligence and essentially vouch for a company.
default 
defaultHow do you tackle the inevitable conflict of interest if the investment company is also in effect an agent for the company concerned?
defaultDavid Lawtondefault: Sponsors really have two sets of responsibilities.
default 
defaultUnder our regime, they are supervised by us and authorised by us to perform the sponsor activity, and we do quite a lot of supervision of the sponsor activity in relation to those firms.
default 
defaultWhere we feel that the sponsor is not acting in accordance with what we want, then we have the ability to take action including discipline.
default 
defaultThe second responsibility is the one that you have just mentioned, which is facing off to the issuer.
default 
defaultSponsors have that dual responsibility.
default 
default&#xa0;
defaultQ148 default&#xa0; 
defaultAnn defaultMcKechindefault:default Has any company faced discipline?
defaultDavid Lawtondefault: Yes.
default&#xa0;
defaultQ149 default&#xa0; 
defaultAnn defaultMcKechindefault:default Have any companies been barred from being sponsors?
defaultDavid Lawtondefault: The new Financial Services and Markets Act, which came into effect in April of this year, has strengthened our ability to both restrict the range of areas where a sponsor could offer services, if we felt that was necessary, but also to suspend a sponsor’s activity and ultimately take them off the list.
defaultAnn defaultMcKechindefault:default Which you had not had previously.
defaultDavid Lawtondefault: Which we did not have previously; that is right.
default 
default&#xa0;
defaultQ150 default&#xa0; 
defaultAnn defaultMcKechindefault:default Have you considered the argument for insisting that sponsors be independent from the applicant companies themselves, particularly if much of their activity is actually 
defaultoutwith
default the 
defaultUK
