defaultDavid Lawtondefault: Typically, a company will list in its home market but, if it wants to broaden the base of investors that have an opportunity to invest in it and perhaps seek a larger pool of capital, it might seek to list in another location.
default 
defaultThat is a trend that is less prevalent these days, because it is now a bit easier for investors to invest in markets elsewhere than their home market.
default 
